    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix IMEISV encoding/decoding in 5G Mobile Identity handling\n\n### Summary\nThe 5G NAS Mobile Identity handling for IMEISV type had incorrect bit field positioning in the encoding function and was missing a decode implementation entirely. This caused incorrect IMEISV values to be sent to the network during registration procedures.\n\nThe root cause was that the `encode_imeisv_5gs_mobile_identity` function was incorrectly placing the typeofidentity, oddeven, and digittac01 fields in the wrong bit positions of the first octet, not matching the structure definition in `Imeisv5GSMobileIdentity_t`. Additionally, there was no decode function for IMEISV type, causing AssertFatal when trying to decode IMEISV identities.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/FGSMobileIdentity.c`: Fixed bit field positioning in `encode_imeisv_5gs_mobile_identity` and added `decode_imeisv_5gs_mobile_identity` implementation.\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/FGSMobileIdentity.c`: Updated `decode_5gs_mobile_identity` to handle IMEISV type.\n\n"
}